<H1>
  Bob's Favorite Films
</H1>

<p> They seem to fall into pretty natural categories.  The emphasis
seems to be on intensity, with a definite weakness for the tragic
hero.  Too bad my favorite character, Batman, has never made a good
film.

<H3>Top Ten</H3>
<UL>
<li> A Clockwork Orange
<li> Groundhog's Day
<li> The Philadelphia Story
<li> Three Days of the Condor
<li> The Usual Suspects
<li> All that Jazz
<li> Betty Blue
<li> Memento
<li> Kagemusha
<li> 2001: A Space Odyssey
</UL>

<H3>Runners Up</H3>
<UL>
<li> Trading Places
<li> Failsafe
<li> Terminator 2
<li> Dead Ringers
<li> Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid
<li> The Jungle Book
<li> Star Wars
</UL>

